{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 17:53:44.227826", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Overall network control-plane and core data-plane appear healthy. EBGP sessions between leaves, spines, and the super-spine are established and exchanging routes as expected.\\n- A single endpoint, pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24), is unreachable. The failure is localized to the access segment between leaf_router_0_1 and pc_0_1. Root cause is on the host: its NIC is down and it is not responding to ARP. A secondary issue on the host is the absence of a default route.\\n\\nObserved Symptoms\\n- Baseline reachability across the fabric is good:\\n  - Multiple hosts can reach 10.1.1.2 with 0% loss and reasonable RTTs (from get_reachability).\\n- Targeted tests involving 10.0.1.2 fail:\\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: 100% loss with ICMP “Destination Host Unreachable” sourced by 172.16.0.35 (leaf_router_0_1’s interface), indicating the egress leaf cannot reach its directly connected host.\\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: “ping: connect: Network is unreachable” (from pc_0_1), indicating missing routing on the host. Additionally, the host interface is down.\\n\\nControl-Plane Health (Routers)\\n- leaf_router_0_1 BGP summary:\\n  - Peers up with four neighbors; PfxRcd = 7 per neighbor (show ip bgp summary).\\n- Routing tables on spines and super-spine include 10.0.1.0/24 learned via the correct next-hops toward leaf_router_0_1 (frr_show_ip_route outputs). This confirms 10.0.1.0/24 is correctly advertised and propagated across the fabric.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 routing table:\\n  - Connected route for 10.0.1.0/24 via eth4 (10.0.1.1).\\n  - BGP-learned routes to other tenant/host subnets present.\\n\\nData-Plane/Host-Edge Findings\\n- leaf_router_0_1 attempting to reach 10.0.1.2:\\n  - Ping to 10.0.1.2 from leaf fails.\\n  - ARP state shows “10.0.1.2 dev eth4 INCOMPLETE” (no ARP replies), confirming L2 adjacency failure toward the host.\\n- pc_0_1 interface and IP stack:\\n  - eth0 has IP 10.0.1.2/24 but its state is DOWN (ip addr shows eth0 state DOWN).\\n  - Interface flags show no UP; RX/TX counters are zero.\\n  - No routes configured at all (ip route is empty), hence “Network is unreachable” when sending to off-subnet destinations.\\n\\nLocalization\\n- Faulty segment: leaf_router_0_1 eth4 <-> pc_0_1 eth0.\\n- Network core (leaves, spines, super-spine, EBGP sessions, and inter-router links) is functioning normally.\\n- Only subnet 10.0.1.0/24’s host 10.0.1.2 is affected; the leaf’s L3 SVI/port (10.0.1.1/24 on eth4) is up, but the host-side NIC is down and not responding.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Primary: pc_0_1’s NIC (eth0) is down, preventing ARP resolution and any L2/L3 traffic to/from the host.\\n- Secondary: pc_0_1 has no default route configured, which would prevent off-subnet communication even if the interface were up.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- Service impact is isolated to pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2). No evidence of broader control-plane or fabric-wide data-plane issues. All other tested paths in the Clos fabric are normal., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='0c767d7b-5b3c-4132-840b-2d9724216cb6'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
